post_text: Time to reveal the 2019 Inductees. Tom Catlin was a member of the 1950 National Champion Oklahoma Sooner, the team that started the championship tradition at Oklahoma. After a pro career at the Cleveland Browns he became an assistant coach at West Point. Tom Catlin's stint at West point was followed by assistant coach duties at the Dallas Texans, Los Angeles Rams, the Buffalo Bills, and the Seattle Seahawks. If you would like to purchase tickets for the banquet inducting the 2019 Hall of Fame class contact the Ponca City School Board at (580) 767-8000. The proceeds from the banquet will be used to fund scholarships the Ponca City's next great class of graduates. #ourgraduateschangetheworld.

post_text:
Po-Hi Hall of Fame's Purpose
We've had a few people ask as to our purpose so I thought we would spell it out here.

1. Honor those who have made extraordinary contributions to their chosen professional careers
2. To serve as inspiration to current and future Po-Hi students as examples of what hard work and persistence can achieve.
3. The creation of an endowed scholarship fund to propel each and every generation of graduates here after to make significant contributions to society.

Po-Hi has graduated a tremendous number of people worthy of this honor. Our nomination list is well over 100. Once a person has been nominated their name will continue to be considered each and every year. If you would like to nominate someone for this honor there is a form pinned at the top of the page. Fill it out so our induction committee can consider that person.

One thing that has impressed me as I have read through the inductees biographies is how successful our athletes were outside of the sports they played or coached. There is not a better representative than Charles Bowman on that account.. He lost a lung and a spleen to a drunk driver and yet still played for what is considered the greatest college football team to ever take the field.
I haven't talked to the Chamber today to find out if any tickets are left or not. I can't image there are very many if we do. We are working on live streaming the banquet on our Facebook page for those that live far away or couldn't make it for whatever reason. More on that next week. #ourgraduateschangetheworld.

post_text: Donald Puddy was an integral part at the greatest scientific and technological achievement of mankind. He played roles in the Gemini, Apollo, and Space Shuttle eras at NASA. He was one of the Engineers who helped guide the Lunar Module to land on the first lunar landing in Apollo 11 and later became the Flight Director at the end of the Apollo era and the beginning of the Space Shuttle Era. He also won the Presidential Medal of Freedom, the highest honor that can be awarded a civilian for his role in Apollo 13. The banquet honoring this great Po-Hi graduate will be on September 27th. Tickets are available at the Ponca City Chamber of Commerce. #ourgraduateschangetheworld

post_text:
The Ponca City High School Hall of Fame committee has been established to bring honor to a Ponca City High School alumni, living or deceased, who has achieved outstanding accomplishments in their career. In honoring these individuals, part of the plan is to exhibit their pictures in a prominent place at Po-Hi which hopefully will be an inspiration to students as they pass through the halls of Po-Hi now and in the future.
The first induction ceremony will be held Thursday, September 28th at 7 p.m. at the Carolyn Renfro Center. Tickets will be $50 per person or $500 for a table of 8. Rich Cantillon, 1976 Po-Hi Alumni, has agreed to head the committee putting together the induction ceremony.
Nomination forms are available at the Ponca City Chamber of Commerce office. Chuck Bowman, 1954 Po-Hi alumni, will head the nomination committee. Plans are to induct 5 – 10 alumni this first year. Deadline for nominations is June 1. Please help by passing this info on to other alumni.
